>>42016878

>Review of 'CoyoteXHuman' by Aabroskiaa
https://www.sofurry.com/view/1688577

I liked this story, the plot's basic but that's not a bad thing for a short smut piece. The erotica was good and quite arousing. Over explained in some areas but overall hot and sexy. I liked it.

I also liked how Anna has coyote features and mannerisms that set her apart from a human. Many furry writers tend to describe a human with animal features when writing anthros. You managed to keep them different. Good job.

However there are some things that can be improved.

Some of the sentences can feel a little long and some comma displacement can read awkwardly. This can be seen in the first sentence where it's hard for the reader to know who is being referred to.

The tense is inconsistent, changing from past to present. While not obvious it can be distracting.

Another thing is there's unnecessary wording that slows the pace without adding anything. An example "and her grip on you has gotten tighter" could be shortened to "and her grip around you tightened." Or "her moans seem to have gotten deeper" could be shortened to "her moans deepened." It's an easy habit to have that I've been guilty of, but it can be broken with practice.

>Review of 'Anything':

There's not much to review but it's a nice little follow up. Also there's some parts were it turns into third person POV.

Overall, I enjoyed the stories and I recommend them.
Anonymous
